<article>
    <h1>New law al&#xAD;lows small busi&#xAD;nesses to rene&#xAD;go&#xAD;ti&#xAD;ate con&#xAD;tracts Covid-19 ( Tem&#xAD;po&#xAD;rary Mea&#xAD;sures) Act</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201104/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-04"><time>2020-11-04</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Re-Align Frame­work will em­power small and mi­cro busi­nesses to rene­go­ti­ate some com­mer­cial con­tracts that were en­tered into be­fore March 25. It was passed in Par­lia­ment yes­ter­day as part of the third set of amend­ments to the Covid-19</p>
    <p>( Tem­po­rary Mea­sures) Act.</p>
    <p>Six-month re­lief pe­riod for busi­nesses and in­di­vid­u­als against le­gal and en­force­ment ac­tion if they are un­able to ful­fil cer­tain con­trac­tual obli­ga­tions due to Covid-19</p>
    <p>Rental re­lief frame­work to help SMEs hit by Covid-19 have their rental waived in a man­dated co-shar­ing of rental obli­ga­tions be­tween the Gov­ern­ment, land­lords and ten­ants</p>
    <p>Sec­ond set of amend­ments passed in Septem­ber Asses­sors ap­pointed by Min­istry of Law get en­hanced pow­ers to spec­ify the amount of rent to be waived un­der the rental re­lief frame­work in some cases</p>
    <p>Third set of amend­ments passed yes­ter­day</p>
    <p>Re-Align Frame­work: Al­lows small and mi­cro busi­nesses hit by Covid-19 to ter­mi­nate their con­tracts early, if par­ties can­not agree on new terms</p>
    <p>Sim­pli­fied In­sol­vency Pro­gramme: Helps fi­nan­cially dis­tressed small and mi­cro com­pa­nies in two ways:</p>
    <p>Re­struc­tur­ing of their debts and po­ten­tial re­ha­bil­i­ta­tion of vi­able busi­nesses</p>
    <p>Or­derly wind­ing-up of non-vi­able busi­nesses</p>


